obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30522)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30522&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi and`
  line `Ajmer-Merwara Land Development Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the ^1[States] of Delhi and ^2[Ajmer].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force in each of the said ^1[States] on such date^3`
  line `as the Chief Commissioner of`
  line `that ^4[State] may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Provinces".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "Ajmer-Merwara".`
  line
  line `3.1st November, 1948, vide notification No. F 14 (108)/A146, dated 29th October, 1948, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30523)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30523&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Land Development Board constituted for the ^2[State] under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "owner", in relation to any land, means--`
  line
  line `(i) a person having a proprietary right in the land and includes a usufructuary mortgagee of`
  line `such right and, in the ^2[State] of ^1[Ajmer], an istimrardar, a jagirdar a muafidar, and a bhumia;`
  line and
  line
  line `(ii) a tenant of the land as hereinafter defined;`
  line
  line `(c) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "reclamation" includes cultivation, afforestation and any other improvement of land; and`
  line
  line `(e) "tenant" includes a usufructuary mortgagee of the rights of a tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs., ibid., for "Ajmer-Merwara".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30524)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Land Development Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30524&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of`
  line `this Act, the Chief Commissioner shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint an officer to be`
  line `called the Land Development Commissioner and constitute for the ^1[State] a Land Development Board`
  line `consisting of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Land Development Commissioner, who shall be the Chairman of the Board,`
  line
  line `(b) two official members who shall be persons of experience in agriculture or irrigation`
  line `engineering, and`
  line
  line `(c) two non-official members.`
  line
  line `(2) A non-official member may, at any time by notice in writing to the Chairman, resign his office.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chief Commissioner may, at any time, remove from the Board any member who is guilty of`
  line `any action involving moral turpitude.`
  line
  line `(4) No act done by the Board shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) If there is a difference of opinion among the members of the Board regarding any question the`
  line `decision of the majority of the members present and voting shall prevail, and in case of equality of votes`
  line `the Chairman shall have a casting vote.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board may appoint one of the official members to be the Secretary of the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) The Chief Commissioner may invest the Land Development Commissioner with all or any of the`
  line `powers of a Deputy Commissioner or a Collector under any law for the time being in force in the ^2[State]`
  line `of Delhi or ^3[Ajmer], as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `3. Subs., ibid., for "Ajmer-Merwara".`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30525)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Matters for which land development schemes may provide.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30525&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Board shall prepare a land`
  line `development scheme for the ^1[State] providing for one or more of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) preservation and improvement of soil;`
  line
  line `(ii) prevention of soil erosion;`
  line
  line `(iii) improvement of water supply by the utilization of water in rivers or rivulets, tube-wells,`
  line `boring or construction of wells, conservation of rain water by constructing dams, or by use of power;`
  line
  line `(iv) improvement in the methods of cultivation;`
  line
  line `(v) introduction of dry farming methods;`
  line
  line `(vi) supply of seed, improved implements of agriculture, manure and fertilizers;`
  line
  line `(vii) development of horticulture and planting of fruit trees;`
  line
  line `(viii) reclamation of land lying waste through water-logging, accumulation of sand, growth of`
  line `jungle, soil erosion or any other cause.`
  line
  line `(ix) cultivation of land lying uncultivated owing to the negligence or incapacity or absence of the`
  line owner;
  line
  line `(x) regulation or prohibition of grazing and browsing;`
  line
  line `(xi) control and maintenance of tree-growth.`
  line
  line `(xii) regulation or prohibition of firing of vegetation;`
  line
  line `(xiii) planting or sowing of trees, shrubs and grasses for the purpose of afforesting uncultivable`
  line `land or providing shelter-beds against wind or sand or for any other purpose;`
  line
  line `(xiv) protection from locusts and other pests; and`
  line
  line `(xv) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every scheme prepared under sub-section (1) shall contain the following particulars, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the objects of the scheme;`
  line
  line `(ii) details of the area to be covered by the scheme;`
  line
  line `(iii) the work or kind of work to be carried out under the scheme;`
  line
  line `(iv) the agency or agencies through which the work shall be carried out;`
  line
  line `(v) the approximate estimated cost of the scheme and the method of financing it;`
  line
  line `(vi) the duties and obligations, financial or other, of the Government as well as of the owners of`
  line `the area concerned; and`
  line
  line `(vii) any other particulars which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30526)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Inquiry into, and sanctioning of, schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30526&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner shall, after the Board`
  line `has prepared the scheme under section 4--`
  line
  line `(a) appoint an Inquiry Officer, and`
  line
  line `(b) cause the scheme to be published in the manner prescribed inviting suggestions from persons`
  line `affected by it within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Commissioner shall, after considering the record of the inquiry and the report of the`
  line `Inquiry Officer and after consulting the Board, submit the scheme with his report to the Central`
  line `Government which may either sanction the scheme with or without modification or reject it.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30527)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Publication of schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30527&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every scheme sanctioned under section 5 shall be published by the`
  line `Land Development Commissioner in the prescribed manner and shall come into force on such date as`
  line `may be specified by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30528)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30528&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Board may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `regulations for the purpose of carrying out the objects of the scheme or in respect of any matter`
  line `supplementary or incidental thereto, and any regulations so made shall also be published by the Board in`
  line `the manner prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (30529)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to make grant of advance loan.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30529&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Land Development Commissioner may, with`
  line `the approval of the Board, make a grant or advance a loan to any person for carrying out any work under`
  line `any scheme on such terms and conditions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount of loan, or any instalment thereof or interest thereon which may be due but not repaid`
  line `in accordance with the terms and conditions of the loan may, without prejudice to any other remedy`
  line `provided by law, be recovered as arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30530)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30530&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) In making any scheme or any regulation under section 7, the Board may provide that`
  line `the contravention of such provisions of the scheme or of such regulations as may be specified by it, shall`
  line `be punishable with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one month, or with fine which`
  line `may extend to fifty rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall be prosecuted for any contravention specified in sub-section (1) except on`
  line `complaint in writing by the Land Development Commissioner.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (30531)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Works to be carried out by Government at owner's expense.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30531&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where under the scheme`
  line `any work is to be carried out on any land at the expense of the owner or owners thereof, and such owner,`
  line `or any of such owners, is willing to carry out the work, he may give notice to that effect in writing to the`
  line `Land Development Commissioner within twenty-one days of the coming into force of the scheme.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of such notice the Land Development Commissioner shall furnish the owner with full`
  line `details of the work, and fix the date before which the owner shall carry out the work.`
  line
  line `(3) If the owner fails to carry out the work to the satisfaction of the Land Development Commissioner`
  line `before the date fixed by him, or if the owner at any time informs the Land Development Commissioner in`
  line `writing of his inability to do so, the Land Development Commissioner may get the work carried out by`
  line `such agency as he thinks fit and the expenses incurred by him in carrying out the work shall be recovered`
  line `from the owner as arrears of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any work is carried out in pursuance of this section by one or more of several owners, the`
  line `other owners shall be liable to contribute towards the expenses incurred by him or them such amount as`
  line `the Board may determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (30532)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Contribution by owners of other land benefiting by work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30532&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Where under the scheme any`
  line `work is carried out by the owner or by the Land Development Commissioner at the expense of the owner,`
  line `and the work is in the opinion of the Board likely to benefit any other land in the area covered by the`
  line `scheme, the owners of such other land shall be liable to contribute towards the expenses of carrying out`
  line `the work such amount as the Board may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chief Commissioner may remit the whole or any part of the contribution so payable`
  line `in respect of any work carried out on land belonging to the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (30533)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Recovery of contributions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30533&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The amount of contribution determined by the Board under subsection (4) of section 10 or section 11 shall be paid by the persons concerned within such time as may be`
  line `specified by the Board, and in default of such payment shall be recovered from those persons as arrears of`
  line `land revenue and paid to the persons entitled to the contribution.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (30534)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to carry out works and recover expenses from owners.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30534&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the scheme, the Board may direct that the work to be carried out or remaining to be carried`
  line `out or any land by the owners thereof shall be carried out by the Land Development Commissioner, and`
  line `that the whole or any specified part of the expenses of carrying out the work shall be recovered as arrears`
  line `of land revenue from the owners of the land in such proportion, at such times, and in such instalments, as`
  line `the Board may fix, having regard to the amount to be recovered and the nature and extent of the rights of`
  line `the owners in the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (30535)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Statement and map showing details of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30535&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the completion of any work under the`
  line `scheme, the Land Development Commissioner shall prepare--`
  line
  line `(a) a statement in such form, and containing such particulars, as may be prescribed, and`
  line
  line `(b) a map showing the location and other material details of the work.`
  line
  line `(2) Every statement and map so prepared shall, on approval by the Board, form part of the settlement`
  line `record, or, as the case may be, the record-of-rights of the estates specified in the statement, and the said`
  line `record shall wherever necessary be corrected in accordance with the statement.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (30536)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Repairs and renewals of work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30536&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `If any person shown in a statement prepared under section 14`
  line `as liable to maintain and keep in repair the work fails to effect such repairs or renewals or to do so within`
  line `such time, as the Land Development Commissioner may by order specify, the Land Development`
  line `Commissioner may get the repairs or renewals done by such agency as he thinks fit, and the expenses`
  line `incurred by him in so doing shall be recovered from the said person as arrears of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (30537)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Enhancement of rent on account of improvement effected by work.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30537&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Where any land in`
  line `which a tenant has a right of occupancy has benefited by work carried out under the scheme by or at the`
  line `expense of the owner of the land, and the tenant has not made any contribution to the expenses thereof,`
  line `the Revenue Officer having jurisdiction shall, on application made by the owner in this behalf, enhance,`
  line `in accordance with such principles as may be prescribed, the rent payable by he tenant in respect of the`
  line `land, anything contained in any law to the contrary notwithstanding.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (30538)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Rights of entry, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30538&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any member, officer, subordinate or workman of the Board or any`
  line `other person authorised by the Land Development Commissioner in this behalf may, after giving such`
  line `notice as may be prescribed to the owner in possession of any land, enter upon and survey the land, or do`
  line `any acts, or carry out any work in or on the land for the purpose of preparing, inquiring into or executing`
  line `any land development scheme the provisions of this Chapter.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such member, officer subordinate, workman or person shall be deemed to be a public`
  line `servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (30539)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30539&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by--`
  line
  line `(a) a determination of the Board under sub-section (4) of section 10 or section 11; or`
  line
  line `(b) the making of an entry, or the failure to make an entry, in a statement prepared under`
  line `section 14; or`
  line
  line `(c) the order of the Land Development Commissioner under section 15; or`
  line
  line `(d) the order of a Revenue Officer under section 16,`
  line
  line `may, within the prescribed time and in the prescribed manner, appeal to the prescribed authority, and,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in any law to the contrary, the decision of such authority, and, where`
  line `no appeal is preferred, the determination, order or statement aforesaid shall be final and shall not be called`
  line `in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (30540)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Power of control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30540&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may from time to time call for any report or give`
  line `any direction to the Board, and the Board shall submit such report and carry out such direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (30541)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30541&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `In this Chapter--`
  line
  line `(a) "date of taking possession" means the date on which temporary possession of the land is taken`
  line `on behalf of the Government under section 21;`
  line
  line `(b) "waste-land" means any land lying waste through water-logging, accumulation of sand,`
  line `growth of jungle, soil erosion or any other cause, or lying uncultivated, for not less than three`
  line `consecutive years.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (30542)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Order for taking possession of waste-land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30542&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the board is satisfied that for purposes of`
  line `executing any scheme of reclamation of waste-land sanctioned under section 5, it is necessary that`
  line `temporary possession of any waste-land should be taken, it may, by order in writing, direct the Land`
  line `Development Commissioner to take temporary possession of such land on behalf of the Government on`
  line `such date as may be specified in that order.`
  line
  line `(2) The order shall be made in such form and brought to the notice of the owner of the land in such`
  line `manner, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) On the date specified in the order, the Land Development Commissioner or an officer authorised`
  line `by him shall enter upon and take possession of the land on behalf of the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (30543)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Arrangement for reclamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30543&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `When the land has been taken possession of the Land`
  line `Development Commissioner may, with the approval of the Board, arrange for its reclamation--`
  line
  line `(a) by retaining it under his management for such period as he thinks fit, or`
  line
  line `(b) by settling it for such period and on such terms as may be fixed by the Board with the person`
  line `who on the date of taking possession was in lawful possession of the land, or was entitled to such`
  line `possession, or, if such person is dead, with his successor in interest, or`
  line
  line `(c) if such person refuses to take the land for such period or on such terms, by settling it with any`
  line `other person, or`
  line
  line `(d) by a combination of the methods aforesaid:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total period for which the land is retained or settled under this section shall not`
  line `exceed ten years.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (30544)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Claim for arrears of rent not to be enforced against Government, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30544&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `No claim of the`
  line `landlord to any arrears of rent accrued or due in respect of the land for the period prior to the date of`
  line `taking possession shall thereafter be enforced by any court, whether in execution of a decree or otherwise,`
  line `against the Government or against any person holding the land under the Government, or by the issue of`
  line `any process against the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (30545)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Termination of possession on completion of reclamation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30545&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the reclamation of the`
  line `land is in the opinion of the Land Development Commissioner complete and, in any case, before the`
  line `expiry of a period of ten years from the making an inquiry in the prescribed manner and by order in`
  line writing,--
  line
  line `(a) declare that possession of the land shall be restored on such date as may be specified in the`
  line `order to the owner who on the date of taking possession was in lawful possession of the land, or was`
  line `entitled to such possession, or if he is dead, to his successor in interest;`
  line
  line `(b) determine the person to whom possession is to be so restored;`
  line
  line `(c) where such person is a tenant, determine the rent payable on account of the use or occupation`
  line `of the land; and`
  line
  line `(d) where the land or any part thereof has been afforested, regulate the cutting of trees in such`
  line land.
  line
  line `(2) On the date specified in the said order, possession of the land shall be deemed to have been`
  line `delivered by the Government to the person determined under clause (b) of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The delivery of possession of the land to the person determined under clause (b) of sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be final and full discharge of the Government from all liability in respect of such delivery, but shall`
  line `not prejudice any right in respect of the land to which any other person may be entitled, by due process of`
  line `law, to enforce against the person to whom the possession of the land has been so delivered.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (30546)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Compensation for period of possession.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30546&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the date of taking`
  line `possession of the land, the Land Development Commissioner shall make an inquiry in the prescribed`
  line `manner and determine--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of any land which on the said date was in the occupation of a tenant--`
  line
  line `(i) the annual rent payable by him, and`
  line
  line `(ii) the average net annual income, if any, after deducting rent derived by him during the`
  line `three years immediately preceding the said date, and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any other land, the average net annual income, if any, without deducting any land`
  line `revenue payable, derived by the owner during the three years immediately preceding the said date.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be payable by the Government as compensation on each anniversary of the date of`
  line `taking possession until the date referred to in sub-section (2) of section 24--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of such land as is referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1), the amount determined`
  line `under sub-clause (i) thereof to the landlord, and the amount determined under sub-clause (ii) thereof`
  line `to the tenant, and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any other land, the amount determined under clause (b) of sub-section (1) to the`
  line owner.
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section "landlord" means the person under whom the tenant holds land`
  line `and to whom the tenant is, or but for a special contract would be, liable to pay rent for that land, and any`
  line `reference to an owner, landlord or tenant shall be deemed to include a reference to the predecessors and`
  line `successors in interest of the owner, landlord or tenant.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (30547)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title Accounts.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30547&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `The Board shall maintain, in such form and in accordance with such rules as may be`
  line `prescribed, an account of all receipts and payments by the Government in respect of the land, and any`
  line `owner of, or other person saving an interest in, the land may, on payment of a fee of eight annas, inspect`
  line `the account.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (30548)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Recovery of net expenditure incurred by Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30548&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The net expenditure incurred by`
  line `the Government on the reclamation of the land under the provisions of this Chapter or such part of that`
  line `expenditure as the Chief Commissioner may by general or special order direct, together with interest`
  line `calculated at the prescribed rate and in the prescribed manner, shall be recovered as arrears of`
  line `land revenue from the person to whom possession of the land delivered by the Government under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 24.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount to be recovered under sub-section (1) from any person shall be decided by the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (30549)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30549&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order under section 21, section 24, section 25 or`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 27 of the Board or the Land Development Commissioner, as the case may be,`
  line `may, within the prescribed time and in the prescribed manner, appeal to the Chief Commissioner, and the`
  line `decision of the Chief Commissioner on such appeal, and where no appeal is preferred the order aforesaid,`
  line `shall be final and shall not be called in question in any court.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (30550)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Continuance of liability for land revenue rates and cesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30550&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The taking and retaining of`
  line `possession of any land on behalf of the Government under provisions of this Chapter shall not affect the`
  line `liability of any person for the payment of land revenue, rate or cess in respect of the land for any period`
  line `whether before or after the date of taking possession.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (30551)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Amendment of Act XVI of 1927 in Delhi.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30551&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The following amendments shall be made in the`
  line `Indian Forest Act, 1927, in its application to the ^1[State] at Delhi, namely:--`
  line
  line `(1) in sub-section (1) of section 35 of the said Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the words any forest or waste-land the words any forest, waste-land or grass-land`
  line `shall be substituted;`
  line
  line `(b) for clauses (b) and (c) the following clauses shall be substituted, namely:--`
  line
  line `"(b) the cutting of trees and timber;`
  line
  line `(c) the disposal of any forest produce;`
  line
  line `(d) the firing or clearing of vegetation;`
  line
  line `(e) the cutting storage and conservation of grass or leaf fodder; or`
  line
  line `(f) the admission, herding or pasturing of Cattle"; and`
  line
  line `(c) after clause (v) the following shall be added:--`
  line
  line `"(vi) for any other purpose conducive to public welfare.";`
  line
  line `(2) in sub-section (2) of section 37 of the said Act, for the words "not less than three" the words "not`
  line `less than seven" shall be substituted; and`
  line
  line `(3) in sub-section (1) of section 38 of the said Act, for the word "two thirds" the word "one-half"`
  line `shall be substituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (30552)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Application of Chapter V, Act XVI of 1927 to Ajmer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30552&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `31. Application of Chapter V, Act XVI of 1927 to ^2[Ajmer].--Without prejudice to the provisions`
  line `of sub-section (3) of section 1 of the Indian Forest Act, 1927, the provisions of Chapter V of that Act`
  line `shall apply to the ^1[State] of ^2[Ajmer] as they apply to the ^1[State] of Delhi.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `2. Subs., ibid., for "Ajmer-Merwara".`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (30553)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30553&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the conduct of business by the Board and the procedure to be followed at meetings of the`
  line Board;
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by Inquiry Officers under section 5;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of publication under sections 5, 6 and 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the principles on which the amounts of contribution are to be determined by the Board under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 10, or section 11;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of the statement under section 14 and the particulars to be stated therein;`
  line
  line `(f) the principles of enhancement of rent under section 16;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of giving notice under sub-section (1) of section 17;`
  line
  line `(h) the authority to whom appeal may lie and the time and manner of such appeal under`
  line `section 18;`
  line
  line `(i) the form of notice under section 21 and the manner of its service;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of inquiry under section 24 and sub-section (1) of section 25;`
  line
  line `(k) the form and method of maintaining accounts under section 26;`
  line
  line `(l) the rate of interest and the method of its calculation under sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(m) the time and manner of appeal under section 28; and`
  line
  line `(n) any matter which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (30554)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056&sectionId=30554&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_23_57_00001_194866_1517807321056
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other proceeding shall lie`
  line `against any person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise expressly provided by or under this Act, no suit or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Government for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything in good faith done`
  line `or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
